dex_entries.sword: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.
dex_entries.shield: It flies on wings of apple skin and spits a powerful acid. It can also change its shape into that of an apple.

dex_entries.sword: Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokémon it preys on.
dex_entries.shield: Its body is covered in sweet nectar, and the skin on its back is especially yummy. Children used to have it as a snack.

dex_entries.sword: When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of sand, it becomes disheartened.
dex_entries.shield: Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.

dex_entries.sword: Capable of generating 15,000 volts of electricity, this Pokémon looks down on all that would challenge it.
dex_entries.shield: It has an electrical organ on its chest. While generating electricity, it fills its surroundings with what sounds like the strumming of a bass guitar.

dex_entries.sword: When this Pokémon sounds as if it’s strumming a guitar, it’s actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.
dex_entries.shield: This short-tempered and aggressive Pokémon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.

dex_entries.sword: Its excessive electric energy is its weapon. This Pokémon can build up more electricity than any thundercloud.
dex_entries.shield: Out of control after its own poison penetrated its brain, it tears across the land in a rampage, contaminating the earth with toxic sweat.

dex_entries.sword: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.
dex_entries.shield: While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.

dex_entries.sword: It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.
dex_entries.shield: If you’re too loud around it, you risk being torn apart by the claws on its tentacle. This Pokémon is also known as the Forest Witch.

location.shield: Giant's Mirror, Hammerlocke Hills, Motostoke Outskirts, Stony Wilderness

dex_entries.sword: With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokémon can overwhelm even Machamp.
dex_entries.shield: Its hairs work like muscle fibers. When its hairs unfurl, they latch on to opponents, ensnaring them as tentacles would.

dex_entries.sword: It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters from a frigid place. It keeps its head iced constantly to make sure it stays nice and cold.
dex_entries.shield: This Pokémon keeps its heat-sensitive head cool with ice. It fishes for its food, dangling its single hair into the sea to lure in prey.

dex_entries.sword: The ice covering this Pokémon’s face has shattered, revealing a slightly worried expression that many people are enamored with.
dex_entries.shield: The hair on its head connects to the surface of its brain. When this Pokémon has something on its mind, its hair chills the air around it.

dex_entries.sword: It uses the horns on its head to sense the emotions of others. Males will act as valets for those they serve, looking after their every need.
dex_entries.shield: Through its horns, it can pick up on the emotions of creatures around it. Positive emotions are the source of its strength.

dex_entries.sword: These intelligent Pokémon touch horns with each other to share information between them.
dex_entries.shield: They diligently serve people and Pokémon so they can gather feelings of gratitude. The females are particularly good at babysitting.

dex_entries.sword: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It’s also generating electricity.
dex_entries.shield: It carries electrically roasted seeds with it as if they’re precious treasures. No matter how much it eats, it always gets hungry again in short order.

dex_entries.sword: Intense hunger drives it to extremes of violence, and the electricity in its cheek sacs has converted into a Dark-type energy.
dex_entries.shield: Hunger hormones affect its temperament. Until its hunger is appeased, it gets up to all manner of evil deeds.

dex_entries.sword: They came over from another region long ago and worked together with humans. Their green skin is resistant to water.
dex_entries.shield: These Pokémon live in herds. Their trunks have incredible grip strength, strong enough to crush giant rocks into powder.

name_origin.arctic: icy region around the North Pole
icy region around the North Pole

dex_entries.sword: Its body resembles polished metal, and it’s both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.
dex_entries.shield: The special metal that composes its body is very light, so this Pokémon has considerable agility. It lives in caves because it dislikes the rain.

dex_entries.sword: Now armed with a weapon it used in ancient times, this Pokémon needs only a single strike to fell even Gigantamax Pokémon.
dex_entries.shield: Able to cut down anything with a single strike, it became known as the Fairy King’s Sword, and it inspired awe in friend and foe alike.

dex_entries.sword: Known as a legendary hero, this Pokémon absorbs metal particles, transforming them into a weapon it uses to battle.
dex_entries.shield: This Pokémon has slumbered for many years. Some say it’s Zamazenta’s elder sister—others say the two Pokémon are rivals.

dex_entries.sword: Its ability to deflect any attack led to it being known as the Fighting Master’s Shield. It was feared and respected by all.
dex_entries.shield: Now that it’s equipped with its shield, it can shrug off impressive blows, including the attacks of Dynamax Pokémon.

dex_entries.sword: In times past, it worked together with a king of the people to save the Galar region. It absorbs metal that it then uses in battle.
dex_entries.shield: This Pokémon slept for aeons while in the form of a statue. It was asleep for so long, people forgot that it ever existed.

dex_entries.sword: The core on its chest absorbs energy emanating from the lands of the Galar region. This energy is what allows Eternatus to stay active.
dex_entries.shield: It was inside a meteorite that fell 20,000 years ago. There seems to be a connection between this Pokémon and the Dynamax phenomenon.

dex_entries.sword: As a result of Rose’s meddling, Eternatus absorbed all the energy in the Galar region. It’s now in a state of power overload.
dex_entries.shield: Infinite amounts of energy pour from this Pokémon’s enlarged core, warping the surrounding space-time.
